@article{vonmoll2024complete,
  abstract = {In the Lady in the Lake scenario, a mobile agent, ùêø, is pitted against an agent, ùëÄ, who is constrained to move along the perimeter of a circle. ùêø is assumed to begin inside the circle and wishes to escape to the perimeter with some finite angular separation from ùëÄ at the perimeter. This scenario has, in the past, been formulated as a zerosum differential game wherein ùêø seeks to maximize terminal separation and ùëÄ seeks to minimize it. Its solution is well-known. However, there is a large portion of the state space for which the canonical solution does not yield a unique equilibrium strategy. This paper provides such a unique strategy by solving an auxiliary zero-sum differential game. In the auxiliary differential game, ùêø seeks to reach a point opposite of ùëÄ at a radius for which their maximum angular speeds are equal (i.e., the antipodal point). ùêø wishes to minimize the time to reach this point while ùëÄ wishes to maximize it. The solution of the auxiliary differential game is comprised of a Focal Line, a Universal Line, and their tributaries. The Focal Line tributaries‚Äô equilibrium strategy for ùêø is semi-analytic, while the Universal Line tributaries‚Äô equilibrium strategy is obtained in closed form.},
